00:03:10.439 --> 00:03:15.739
devices out there. I think the stat came out
in March that there are actually more people,

00:03:15.739 --> 00:03:21.689
at least in the U.S., buying smartphones and
tablets than buying laptop and desktop computers

00:03:21.689 --> 00:03:28.329
today, which is just crazy. It's hard to understate
the impact that this is going to have on computing

00:03:28.329 --> 00:03:32.150
and on society.
So what about apps?

00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:36.749
A few years ago, if you had a great idea for
an app, it was pretty simple. You'd put your

00:03:36.749 --> 00:03:41.419
app up, and maybe you would charge 99 cents
for it or you throw some ads on it and hope

00:03:41.419 --> 00:03:47.069
for the best. But things have gotten a lot
more complicated. There are many ways to monetize

00:03:47.069 --> 00:03:52.680
your app out there. You can sell it, you can
sell stuff within the app, you can do virtual

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:55.700
goods, you can do subscriptions, you can do
advertising.

00:03:55.700 --> 00:04:00.479
So one of the things that we get asked a lot
is, what monetization method should I use?

00:04:00.479 --> 00:04:06.989
So we've thought about this. And we want to
try and show you guys a nice little framework

00:04:06.989 --> 00:04:11.609
for thinking about this.
So here's the framework. It's not all that

00:04:11.609 --> 00:04:17.040
simple.
This flowchart is not meant to be a -- you

00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:23.450
know, a playbook, but it's just an illustration
of how complex the world is out there.

00:04:23.450 --> 00:04:28.120
And, really, the point we're trying to make
is that there's no one path to monetizing

00:04:28.120 --> 00:04:34.590
your app. Different people use apps in very
different ways. Anybody that's looked closely

00:04:34.590 --> 00:04:39.830
at a piece of software knows that people use
it for all sorts of different things. Like,

00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:46.570
users are diverse. And so it's really up to
you guys to understand your users and understand,

00:04:46.570 --> 00:04:52.270
therefore, what are the best ways to monetize
depending on what your users are doing.

00:04:52.270 --> 00:04:56.110
And if there's one thing we really want you
to take away from this session, it is just

00:04:56.110 --> 00:05:01.780
that, that there's no one single path to maximizing
the value you get from your app. But it's

00:05:01.780 --> 00:05:05.850
really about understanding your users and
understanding the best ways to do that, given

00:05:05.850 --> 00:05:08.830
what they're doing.
So let's take an example.

00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:13.670
So let's say you have a group of users that
are, you know, excited about your app and,

00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:20.940
you know, maybe they are, I don't know, pick
