well. Isn't that just amazing?
But having users alone is really not enough.

00:08:04.020 --> 00:08:08.900
What we need to make sure is that they really
have the necessary instruments to pay for

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:16.430
your services. And, in other words, that means
providing different options of forms of payment

00:08:16.430 --> 00:08:22.710
or what we call FOPs, set up that they can
actually very easily pay for your services

00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:26.260
within the Google Play Store.
And also these different forms of payments

00:08:26.260 --> 00:08:33.729
need to suit different user needs as well.
So in the Google Play Store, we've always

00:08:33.729 --> 00:08:40.529
given users the option to charge by credit
card or by debit card. But, of course, not

00:08:40.529 --> 00:08:44.970
everybody has a credit card. Many different
-- many different demographics, different

00:08:44.970 --> 00:08:49.370
locations of users, you know, they don't actually
have access to a credit card.

00:08:49.370 --> 00:08:55.560
So we have added direct carrier billing. And
since last year at Google I/O, we've added

00:08:55.560 --> 00:09:00.300
