00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:55.990
does support in-app billing, then you send
a billing request with something called a

00:18:55.990 --> 00:19:02.400
request purchase, and you get back a bundle
with response code, a purchase intent, and

00:19:02.400 --> 00:19:07.270
a request ID. What the purchase intent is,
remember when we were talking about earlier

00:19:07.270 --> 00:19:11.490
that you -- your application provides the
application interface, but the Google Play

00:19:11.490 --> 00:19:16.170
Store client actually provides the transaction
interface. Okay? So this is where the purchase

00:19:16.170 --> 00:19:23.790
intent comes into play.
Next, you get that intent. You're at the application.

00:19:23.790 --> 00:19:28.330
The user now wants to purchase, let's say,
a sort. And now you start the intent. It goes

00:19:28.330 --> 00:19:35.059
into the Google Play interface. And here's
a quick code snippet of how this will work.

00:19:35.059 --> 00:19:41.071
The first section is setting up that request
purchase. You put in a product ID, and you

00:19:41.071 --> 00:19:47.060
also put in a product type. Product type would
be either it's an in-app or a subscription.

00:19:47.060 --> 00:19:49.620
