00:19:49.620 --> 00:19:55.550
Once you set up the request bundle, then you
basically send it to M SVS. M service is the

00:19:55.550 --> 00:20:00.940
market billing service. You trigger send billing
request, you send over that request, and you

00:20:00.940 --> 00:20:07.160
get back a -- a pending intent. The intent
where you launch the Google Play UI.

00:20:07.160 --> 00:20:19.160
Okay. And then, finally, your application
can pop that up, the screen, for purchasing.

00:20:19.160 --> 00:20:25.140
And when the transaction is completed -- and
"completed," it could mean it actually went

00:20:25.140 --> 00:20:32.150
through or the user somehow cancelled -- you
get a broadcast intent. So the broadcast intent

00:20:32.150 --> 00:20:37.930
is called in-app notify.
